_json.gridTitle: Pigweed Potpourri - Eat The Weeds and other things, too
_json.description: Lambsquarters, pigweed, goosefoot: METHOD OF PREPARATION: Young leaves raw, older leaves sweated or boiled, seeds after soaking overnight and rinsed well to remove saponins on surface. Chenopodium is a nitrogen holding plant  and high in oxalic acid. Best avoided by those with kidney stones, gout or related issues.  Seed is 49% carbohydrate, 16% protein, and 5.88% ash. Water the seeds are soaked in can be used as soap. - via Green Deane on Eat The Weeds
